<p>Makes 4 servings</p>

<p>Prep 15 minutes</p>

<p>Cook 30 minutes</p>

<p>Total 45 minutes</p>

<h3 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h3>

<ul>
  <li>4 medium ripe pears</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons lemon juice</li>
  <li>1/3 cup coarsely chopped walnuts</li>
  <li>1/4 cup golden raisins</li>
  <li>2 tablespoons maple syrup</li>
  <li>2 teaspoons brown sugar</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon grated lemon peel</li>
  <li>1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li>
  <li>1 tablespoon butter</li>
  <li>2/3 cup apple juice</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="instructions">Instructions</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Core pears and peel 1 in. down from the top on each. Brush peeled portion with some of the lemon juice. Place in a greased 1-qt. baking dish.</li>
  <li>In a bowl, combine the walnuts, raisins, syrup, brown sugar, lemon peel, cinnamon and remaining lemon juice. Spoon into pears. Dot with butter. Pour apple juice around pears. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 30-40 minutes or until pears are tender, basting several times.</li>
</ol>

